direction: right
title: |md
  # Connection Duration Tracking Flow
| {near: top-center}
style.fill: "#1a1a2a"
style.stroke: "#333"
style.font-color: white
ESTABLISHED: TCP_ESTABLISHED {
  style.fill: "#4CAF50"
  style.font-color: white
  shape: circle
}
TIME_WAIT: TCP_TIME_WAIT{
  style.fill: "#FF9800"
  style.font-color: white
  shape: circle
}
CLOSE: TCP_CLOSE{
  style.fill: "#F44336"
  style.font-color: white
  shape: circle
}
conn_info: Connection Hash Map{
  shape: cylinder
  style.fill: "#2196F3"
  style.font-color: white
}
event: Ring Buffer Event{
  shape: parallelogram
  style.fill: "#9C27B0"
  style.font-color: white
}
ESTABLISHED -> conn_info: "1. Store timestamp\n   skaddr → established_ts\n   + PID, comm, 4-tuple"
conn_info -> conn_info: "2. Connection active\n   data in hash map"
conn_info -> TIME_WAIT: "3. State change\n   TIME_WAIT or CLOSE"
TIME_WAIT -> conn_info: "4. Lookup by skaddr\n   retrieve established_ts"
conn_info -> event: "5. Compute duration\n   duration_ns = now - established_ts\n   + copy 4-tuple, PID"
event -> conn_info: "6. Submit to ring buffer\n   bpf_ringbuf_submit(event)"
conn_info -> conn_info: "7. Delete hash entry\n   bpf_map_delete_elem(&connections, &skaddr)"
note: |md
  **Key:** Socket pointer (skaddr)
  **Maps:** Hash for correlation, Ringbuf for events
  **States:** ESTABLISHED → tracking → TIME_WAIT/CLOSE → cleanup
| {near: bottom-center}
style.fill: "#1a1a2a"
style.font-color: white
style.stroke: "#333"